      "raw_text": "The petition of the Spokane\nAmateur Athletic club to vacate a\ntriangular strip Of ground on the\nsoutheast corner of Main avenue\nand Monroe street was referred to\nthe committee of the Whole by the\ncity council last night. Corpora\nton Counsel Geragherty announced\nthat to make the vacation the writ\nten consent of property owners on\nboth sides of the avenue would\nhave to be obtained.\n\n\nCorporation Counsel Geragherty\nwas instructed to advise the coun-\nGil at it's next meeting whether the\nrailroad could could be compelled\nto pay the expenses of viaduct\nacross the tracks on Division street\nnorth of the river.\n\n\nCouncilman Funk introduced a\nresolution calling upon the board\nof public works to prepare plans\nfor paving Sprague avenue from\nBrowne to Grant street.\n\n\nLast night was the last regular\nsession Of the present city council.\nIt adjourned until Friday morning."
    }
